For each protein, please run `fpocket` to identify pockets and find the 'Druggability Score' of its top-ranked pocket. Return the PDB ID of the protein that has the single highest druggability score among the group. Format: `<answer>str</answer>`.

input: To understand the solution dynamics of the NMR ensemble structure `2K39`, we will analyze its flexibility. Please calculate the per-residue Root Mean Square Fluctuation (RMSF) across all models. Then, identify the most flexible contiguous 5-residue region by finding the window with the highest average RMSF. If multiple regions have identical maximum average RMSF values (ties), return all tied starting positions as a comma-separated string of integers, sorted in ascending order. If there is only one maximum region, return just that single residue number. Format: `<answer>str</answer>`.

Please determine the Relative Solvent Accessibility (RSA) for the wild-type residue of each variant and identify which variant corresponds to the most buried residue (lowest RSA).
